text.section:
The Transportation Cabinet shall not terminate the services of any employee in a job classification which requires a valid commercial driver's license if:
The employee has never held an operator's license;
The employee is not eligible for a medical waiver to operate a commercial vehicle;
The employee's driving record as of March 31, 1992, precludes the issuance of a commercial driver's license;
The employee's job description, as of April 1, 1992, does not require a commercial driver's license;
The employee retires by December 31, 1992.
